docs.summary:
Returns an array of Media Display URLs.
  The body of the request needs to include at least one item ID.

  A Media Display URL is only valid for 15 minutes.
  In case it has expired, a `410 HTTP status` will be returned including the `{ message: "expired" }` hint.

  If you want to increment the view count when retrieving a Media Display URL you’ll need to pass `incrementViewCount:true` in the body of the request.
  The default is `incrementViewCount:false`.

examples.title: Get visual media view URL
body:
curl -X POST https://www.wixapis.com/shared-gallery/v1/visual-media/view  \
    -H 'Content-Type: application/json;charset=UTF-8' \
    -H 'Authorization: QmmUjZPnRwcZnN004ailKKOTR4tNo6fyKcV9kXxC02Q.' \
    --data-binary @- << EOF
{
    "itemIds": ["aa44af34-b5dc-4021-9260-6a0acb7ee156"],
    "incrementViewCount": true
}
EOF

extra.description: Gets expiring url to a picture or video

docs.summary:
Returns a Media Download URL.

  The body of the request needs to include at least one item ID.
  When passing multiple IDs, the response will still be a single download URL that points to a zip archive.
  All requested media will be located on the archive’s root level.
  Your app can start the download immediately, even if the zip process has not finished yet.

  A Media Download ULR is only valid for 15 minutes.
  In case it has expired, a `410 HTTP status` will be returned including the `{ message: "expired" }` hint.

  Calling the **Get Media Download URL** endpoint does not increment the view count of a media item.

examples.title: Get urls to download albums or visual media

extra.description: Download whole album or individual visual media in archive

Possible values are:
  • DEFAULT_REASON - No exact reason. Depends on status if action is ALLOWED or FORBIDDEN
  • NOT_ALLOWED_ON_ROOT - This action is not allowed because it tried on root folder
  • MISSING_PERMISSION - Site member is missing permission to perform action
  • MUST_BE_PUBLIC - Site member who is performing this action is private so it is not allowed because it will expose site member
  • OWNED_BY_ANOTHER_USER - Only available for item owners
  • ALBUM_NOT_EMPTY - Can't delete non empty album
  • MUST_BE_A_MEMBER - Additionally is_allowed_for_all_members will be set if all members are granted this action Usually this means user must log in in order to perform this action
  • NOT_ALLOWED_ON_SUBFOLDERS_THIS_DEEP - Action only available on root or first level subfolders
  • NOT_ALLOWED_ON_FILES - Action only available on subfolders
  • NOT_FOUND - Library item is not found

Possible values are:
  • ALLOWED - Action is allowed
  • FORBIDDEN - Action is forbidden without any specific reason

  • UPLOAD_VISUAL_MEDIA - Grants permission to upload visual media to the gallery
  • MODERATE - Makes role a manager role that can do all the actions in the gallery
  • CREATE_ALBUM - Allows to create albums

Possible values are:
  • ALL_MEMBERS
  • ADMINS
  • CUSTOM
  • PLAN
  • MEMBER
  • SITE_VISITORS
  • BADGE
